The paper proposes a novel approach for domain adaptation in brain-computer interfaces (BCIs), which involves aligning the label space of the source domain with that of the target domain. This is a machine learning problem, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques to develop the proposed approach. The use of BCIs also suggests that the paper may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques to extract features from the BCI data, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it deals with the development of BCIs, which suggests that it may belong to this sub-category as well.
